cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with optimization of input alphabets and energy penalty minimization for the Gaussian MIMO broadcast channel. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper discusses non-cooperative users and the impact of precoding on spectral efficiency. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with the analysis of the MIMO broadcast channel and the impact of precoding on channel output. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of precoding on signal-to-noise ratios and spectral efficiency. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the optimization of a transmitter system with a linear front-end and nonlinear precoding.
